race.comment: The fillies and mares division of the 1200m maiden and it looks a bit deeper than the boys' contest. SENSATIONAL SECRET (8) was beaten as an odds-on favourite last start but was hardly disgraced when less than a length off the winner. With the benefit of that run and back into a provincial class maiden, she can improve here and looks the one to beat. LADY ZELDA (4) finished ahead of SENSATIONAL SECRET last start and is an improving type. She's drawn low and can get all the favours again with a cosy run for Crowther. Expect she will be somewhere in the finish. FOREVER A DIAMOND (11) was much better last start and could be starting to put it together. She looks a top three chance. MRS PENNY CRACKER (5) looks ready to peak and can run a cheeky race at a price.
